    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 143</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.13/1–1351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d143fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_GGMM1"
                            >Godley</persName> and cleared with Lacy, Director of the Office of
                        Philippine and Southeast Asian Affairs.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 15, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3732. For Amb. ReEmbtel 4032 Jan 13<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Pres today approved ur extending
                    invitation to <persName corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> Jan 29–30 informal
                    visit Wash.</p>
                <p>Regret inability offer choice dates but Jan 29–30 are only days within suggestion
                    last para <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> and after <persName
                        corresp="#p_EGDD1">Eisenhower</persName> has reported.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d143fn3">For documentation on <persName corresp="#p_EGDD1"
                            >Eisenhower</persName>’s tour of various <gloss target="#t_NAT1"
                            >NATO</gloss> capitals in January 1951, see <ref
                            target="frus1951v03p1#pg_392">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, Part
                            1, pp. 392</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>If convenient to you it wld be helpful to us if you could be here for visit.</p>
                <pb facs="0338" n="296" xml:id="pg_296"/>
                <p>Wld appreciate further detailed info on subjects <persName corresp="#p_PR2"
                        >Pleven</persName> desires discuss. Submit any items you believe Pres or Sec
                    shld raise that are not on <persName corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName>’s list.
                    Who will accompany him.</p>
                <p>View press speculation hope visit will not leak pending issuance coordinated
                    Wash–Paris communiqué which shld be done soonest. Therefore suggest you consult
                        <persName corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> and submit to Dept brief draft
                    statement to effect that as <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> has indicated
                    desire to discuss with Pres mutual problems Pres has invited <persName
                        corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> visit Wash Jan 29–30,<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d143fn4">In telegram 4083 from Paris, January 16, Ambassador
                            <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">Bruce</persName> reported that <persName
                            corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> had accepted “with great pleasure”
                        the invitation to visit Washington between January 29 and 30 and that
                        detailed information on subjects he wished to discuss with the President and
                        other American officials would be sent to Washington as soon as possible.
                        (751.13/1–1651)</note> etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
